function y = sigmoid(params, x)%y = sigmoid(params, x)%% Returns y, the model values at each of the input x values% given parameter values 'params'. %% params = [s,p,m] where s is the semi-saturation (the stimulus intensity % that will give y of 0.5*m), p is the slope parameter and m is the saturation% (the upper asymtote, the maximum).s = params(1);p = params(2);m = params(3);y = m * (x.^p ./ (x .^ p + s .^ p));